com.mappedin.sdk

Class Coordinate

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.mappedin.sdk.Navigatable
      • com.mappedin.sdk.Coordinate
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Focusable

    public class Coordinate
extends Navigatable
implements Focusable
    A Coordinate represents a 3-dimensional position, anchored to a specific map. If you want a position that is map-independent, consider the Vector3 class.
    See Also:
    Vector3, Navigatable, Focusable

      • Coordinate

        public Coordinate(android.location.Location geoLocation,
                  Map map)
        Take a given lat/lon pair and create a Coordinate attaching it to a specific map.
        code snip:
         android.location.Location geoLocation = new android.location.Location("Mappedin office");
 geoLocation.setLatitude(43.451648);
 geoLocation.setLongitude(-80.495002);
 Coordinate coordinate = new Coordinate(geoLocation, venue.getMaps()[0]);
        Parameters:
        geoLocation - The Android location object, with latitude and longitude
        map - The map this geo-referenced position belongs to.

        Parameters:

        2D euclidean distance in meters
        Throws:

      • metersFrom

        public float metersFrom(Polygon polygon)
                 throws MappedInException
        Returns the 2D euclidean distance in meters from this Coordinate to the closest point on the edge of a Polygon. If negative, the Coordinate is inside the Polygon, if positive the Coordinate is outside.
        Parameters:
        polygon - The polygon to be used in the distance calculation
        Returns:
        distance in meters
        Throws:
        MappedInException - when the coordinate and polygon belongs to different maps.

      • metersFrom

        public float metersFrom(Coordinate[] path)
                 throws MappedInException
        Returns the 2D euclidean distance in meters from this Coordinate to the closest point on a path represented by an array of Coordinate line segments.
        Parameters:
        path - An array of Coordinates that make up the line segments of the path
        Returns:
        Distance in meters
        Throws:
        MappedInException - when none of the coordinate in the array is in the same map as this coordinate.
